      "content": "i mean, even if the history is \"incomplete,\" isn't that still better than just letting judges decide what they want based on how they feel about guns today? one is based on actual evidence from the 1700s, and the other is just... whatever. wouldn't you say the living constitution approach is fundamentally less legitimate because it lacks that historical anchor?",
